Vintage cocktail selection found only at @thedonovanbar has been carefully curated by @cocktailmaestro himself. 

The crowning glory of the vintage menu is ‘Salvatore’s Legacy’, a cocktail that in 2012 broke the Guinness World Record for the most expensive cocktail with a Cognac-based drink priced at £5,500 a glass. 
•
Credit to @thedonovanbar 
•
Made using the bar’s oldest spirit, a 1788 Clos de Griffier Vieux cognac, as well as Dubb Orange liqueur (c1860) and a dash of Angostura Bitters (c1930), this original creation of Salvatore’s offers more than 700 years of liquid history.

On Friday, The Donovan Bar made history once again with @federico_pvn having the opportunity of preparing ‘Salvatore’s legacy’.

An amazing and historial moment for the team! 

Salute 🍸

Another twist and this time on "Penicillin" - “Islay Tea”
-45ml Scotch whiskey infused Bergamot tea
-30ml lemon juice 
-15ml homemade ginger syrup 
-10ml MONIN agave syrup 
-Islay whiskey 2 sprays 
Method: Shake and double strain 
Glass: coupe 
Garnish: spray from Islay whiskey 
Drink responsibly 
•
Credit to @andryuflair 
•
#cocktails #cocktail #bartender #bartending #barskills #behindthebar #bar #work #fihuli #bartenderlife #drink #classiccocktails #twist #flairbartending

Espresso Martini has a relatively short history with the drink believed to have been first created in the early eighties by London bartender Dick Bradsel. According to Dick, a famous model entered the Soho Brasserie where he was working, and asked him to create a drink that would “wake me up” and there it was.

Simply delicious 🤤

node.text:
Vintage cocktail selection found only at @thedonovanbar has been carefully curated by @cocktailmaestro himself. 

The crowning glory of the vintage menu is ‘Salvatore’s Legacy’, a cocktail that in 2012 broke the Guinness World Record for the most expensive cocktail with a Cognac-based drink priced at £5,500 a glass. 
•
Credit to @thedonovanbar 
•
Made using the bar’s oldest spirit, a 1788 Clos de Griffier Vieux cognac, as well as Dubb Orange liqueur (c1860) and a dash of Angostura Bitters (c1930), this original creation of Salvatore’s offers more than 700 years of liquid history.

On Friday, The Donovan Bar made history once again with @federico_pvn having the opportunity of preparing ‘Salvatore’s legacy’.

An amazing and historial moment for the team! 

Salute 🍸
